ds_and_statistics"}
{"title_page": "Pinchi", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Pinchi\n| image = Pinchi.jpg\n| caption = Pinchi in 2017\n| full_name = \u00d3scar Francisco Garc\u00eda Quintela\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1996|1|17|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[A Coru\u00f1a]], Spain\n| height = 1.71 m\n| position = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]]\n| currentclub = [[Extremadura UD|Extremadura]]\n| clubnumber = 16\n| youthyears1 = 2005\u20132015 | youthclubs1 = [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a|Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a]]\n| years1 = 2013\u20132018 | clubs1 = [[Deportivo Fabril|Deportivo B]] | caps1 = 29 | goals1 = 6\n| years2 = 2015\u20132017 | clubs2 = [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a|Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a]] | caps2 = 1 | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2018\u20132019 | clubs3 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid B]] | caps3 = 33 | goals3 = 9\n| years4 = 2019\u2013 | clubs4 = [[Extremadura UD|Extremadura]] | caps4 = 16 | goals4 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = \n| club-update = 22:36, 28 November 2019 (UTC)\n| ntupdate = \n}}\n\n'''\u00d3scar Francisco Garc\u00eda Quintela''' (born 17 Jnauary 1996)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.footballdatabase.eu/fr/joueur/details/282736-oscar-pinchi|title=\u00d3scar Pinchi - Extremadura UD\u00a0 - Stats - palmar\u00e8s|website=www.footballdatabase.eu|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/oscar-pinchi-estamos-con-muchas-ganas-de-que-llegue-el-domingo|title=Club Atl\u00e9tico de Madrid \u00b7 Web oficial - \u00d3scar \u2018Pinchi\u2019: \u201cEstamos con muchas ganas de que llegue el domingo\u201d|website=www.atleticodemadrid.com|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>, commonly known as '''Pinchi''', is a Spanish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays mainly as a [[Midfielder#Winger|left winger]] for [[Extremadura UD]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[A Coru\u00f1a]], [[Galicia, Spain|Galicia]], Pinchi joined [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a]]'s youth setup in 2005 at the age of nine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/torremarathon/2015/11/07/corunes-deportivista-pichichi/0003_201511G7P40991.htm|title=\u00d3scar Garc\u00eda, Pinchi: Coru\u00f1\u00e9s, deportivista y pichichi|trans-title=\u00d3scar Garc\u00eda, Pinchi: ''Coru\u00f1\u00e9s'', ''deportivista'' and ''pichichi''|publisher=[[La Voz de Galicia]]|language=es|date=7 November 2015|accessdate=20 March 2016}}</ref> He made his debut as a senior with [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a B|the reserves]] in 2012, representing the side in [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]].\n\nPinchi made his official debut for the first team on 16 December 2015, coming on as a second-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Luis Alberto (footballer, born 1992)|Luis Alberto]] in a 1\u20131 home draw against [[UE Llagostera]], for [[2015\u201316 Copa del Rey|the season]]'s [[Copa del Rey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2015_16/copa/dieciseisavos/vuelta/dep_lla/|title=El Llagostera roza la sorpresa en Riazor|trans-title=Llagostera near the surprise at the Riazor|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=15 December 2015|accessdate=20 March 2016}}</ref> His [[La Liga]] debut came on 20 January 2017, replacing [[Joselu]] in an away draw against [[UD Las Palmas]] for the same scoreline.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2016_17/la-liga/jornada_19/pal_dep/|title=Andone se cuela en la fiesta de Las Palmas|trans-title=Andone creeps in Las Palmas' party|publisher=Marca|language=es|date=20 January 2017|accessdate=21 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 June 2018, Pinchi left ''D\u00e9por'' and joined [[Atl\u00e9tico de Madrid]], being assigned to [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid B|the reserves]] in [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rcdeportivo.es/noticia/pinchi-se-despide-del-depor|title=Pinchi se despide del D\u00e9por|trans-title=Pinchi leaves ''D\u00e9por''|publisher=Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a|language=es|date=27 June 2018|access-date=29 June 2018}}</ref> On 19 July of the following year, he agreed to a three-year contract with [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] side [[Extremadura UD]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.extremaduraud.com/pinchi-dinamita-y-explosividad-en-azulgrana/|title='Pinchi', dinamita y explosividad en azulgrana|trans-title='Pinchi', firepower in blue-and-red|publisher=Extremadura UD|language=es|date=19 July 2019|accessdate=21 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|20052}}\n*{{LaPreferente|135980<!-- /oscar-pinchi -->}}\n*{{Soccerway|oscar-francisco-garcia-quintela/430182}}\n\n{{Extremadura UD squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pinchi}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from A Coru\u00f1a]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Galician footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n[[Category:La Liga players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Tercera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Deportivo Fabril players]]\n[[Category:Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a players]]\n[[Category:Atl\u00e9tico Madrid B players]]\n[[Category:Extremadura UD footballers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Pinchi\n| image = Pinchi.jpg\n| caption = Pinchi in 2017\n| full_name = \u00d3scar Francisco Garc\u00eda Quintela\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1996|1|17|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[A Coru\u00f1a]], Spain\n| height = 1.71 m\n| position = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]]\n| currentclub = [[Extremadura UD|Extremadura]]\n| clubnumber = 16\n| youthyears1 = 2005\u20132015 | youthclubs1 = [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a|Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a]]\n| years1 = 2013\u20132018 | clubs1 = [[Deportivo Fabril|Deportivo B]] | caps1 = 29 | goals1 = 6\n| years2 = 2015\u20132017 | clubs2 = [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a|Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a]] | caps2 = 1 | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2018\u20132019 | clubs3 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid B]] | caps3 = 33 | goals3 = 9\n| years4 = 2019\u2013 | clubs4 = [[Extremadura UD|Extremadura]] | caps4 = 16 | goals4 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = \n| club-update = 22:36, 28 November 2019 (UTC)\n| ntupdate = \n}}\n\n'''\u00d3scar Francisco Garc\u00eda Quintela''' (born 17 Jnauary1996)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.footballdatabase.eu/fr/joueur/details/282736-oscar-pinchi|title=\u00d3scar Pinchi - Extremadura UD\u00a0 - Stats - palmar\u00e8s|website=www.footballdatabase.eu|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/oscar-pinchi-estamos-con-muchas-ganas-de-que-llegue-el-domingo|title=Club Atl\u00e9tico de Madrid \u00b7 Web oficial - \u00d3scar \u2018Pinchi\u2019: \u201cEstamos con muchas ganas de que llegue el domingo\u201d|website=www.atleticodemadrid.com|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>, commonly known as '''Pinchi''', is a Spanish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays mainly as a [[Midfielder#Winger|left winger]] for [[Extremadura UD]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[A Coru\u00f1a]], [[Galicia, Spain|Galicia]], Pinchi joined [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a]]'s youth setup in 2005 at the age of nine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/torremarathon/2015/11/07/corunes-deportivista-pichichi/0003_201511G7P40991.htm|title=\u00d3scar Garc\u00eda, Pinchi: Coru\u00f1\u00e9s, deportivista y pichichi|trans-title=\u00d3scar Garc\u00eda, Pinchi: ''Coru\u00f1\u00e9s'', ''deportivista'' and ''pichichi''|publisher=[[La Voz de Galicia]]|language=es|date=7 November 2015|accessdate=20 March 2016}}</ref> He made his debut as a senior with [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a B|the reserves]] in 2012, representing the side in [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]].\n\nPinchi made his official debut for the first team on 16 December 2015, coming on as a second-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Luis Alberto (footballer, born 1992)|Luis Alberto]] in a 1\u20131 home draw against [[UE Llagostera]], for [[2015\u201316 Copa del Rey|the season]]'s [[Copa del Rey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2015_16/copa/dieciseisavos/vuelta/dep_lla/|title=El Llagostera roza la sorpresa en Riazor|trans-title=Llagostera near the surprise at the Riazor|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=15 December 2015|accessdate=20 March 2016}}</ref> His [[La Liga]] debut came on 20 January 2017, replacing [[Joselu]] in an away draw against [[UD Las Palmas]] for the same scoreline.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2016_17/la-liga/jornada_19/pal_dep/|title=Andone se cuela en la fiesta de Las Palmas|trans-title=Andone creeps in Las Palmas' party|publisher=Marca|language=es|date=20 January 2017|accessdate=21 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 June 2018, Pinchi left ''D\u00e9por'' and joined [[Atl\u00e9tico de Madrid]], being assigned to [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid B|the reserves]] in [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rcdeportivo.es/noticia/pinchi-se-despide-del-depor|title=Pinchi se despide del D\u00e9por|trans-title=Pinchi leaves ''D\u00e9por''|publisher=Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a|language=es|date=27 June 2018|access-date=29 June 2018}}</ref> On 19 July of the following year, he agreed to a three-year contract with [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] side [[Extremadura UD]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.extremaduraud.com/pinchi-dinamita-y-explosividad-en-azulgrana/|title='Pinchi', dinamita y explosividad en azulgrana|trans-title='Pinchi', firepower in blue-and-red|publisher=Extremadura UD|language=es|date=19 July 2019|accessdate=21 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|20052}}\n*{{LaPreferente|135980<!-- /oscar-pinchi -->}}\n*{{Soccerway|oscar-francisco-garcia-quintela/430182}}\n\n{{Extremadura UD squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pinchi}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from A Coru\u00f1a]]\n[[